---
// Three tools, one idea. Pillar links point at the docs sections until
// dedicated tool routes exist (tracked as a follow-up to the unify migration).
---

<section class="section section--pillars">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">the toolset</p>
    <h2 class="section__title">three tools, one idea.</h2>

    <div class="pillars">
      <a class="pillar pillar--link" href="https://dylanroscover.github.io/Embody/envoy/">
        <h3 class="pillar__name">Envoy</h3>
        <p class="pillar__claim">forward velocity.</p>
        <p class="pillar__body">
          48 MCP tools that plug Claude, Cursor, or Windsurf straight into your live session. Say what you want. Watch it happen. Idea to network in seconds.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a class="pillar pillar--link" href="https://dylanroscover.github.io/Embody/">
        <h3 class="pillar__name">Embody</h3>
        <p class="pillar__claim">lateral velocity.</p>
        <p class="pillar__body">
          Tag any operator and Embody externalizes it to version-control-friendly files on disk. Diff what changed, track who changed it, collaborate across branches, and restore any previous state. Your externalized files are the source of truth &mdash; not the binary <code>.toe</code>.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
      </a>

      <a class="pillar pillar--link" href="https://dylanroscover.github.io/Embody/tdn/specification/">
        <h3 class="pillar__name">TDN</h3>
        <p class="pillar__claim">the substrate.</p>
        <p class="pillar__body">
          TouchDesigner networks as human-readable JSON. Your agent can read it. You can read it. Git can read it.
        </p>
        <span class="pillar__arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
